<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO TOM</font><br>
<tt>Sat Aug 16 10:43:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Tom,<br><br>
Well said.  My son's wife is Asian as is the beautiful grandaughter they have blessed me with.  They still work and live in the Pacific Rim.  I made it a point to not involve my sons in the war and let them develop without my biases.<br><br>
In all my experience I do not remember any personal hatred for the Vietnamese only the enemy, the faceless, nameless, enemy.   I protected myself as did many others by not having personal wars, but I saw those who did and they paid a price.<br><br>
I work today in the defense industry alongside several ex Vietnamese  Officers.  We have talked only briefly about the War.  They chose to leave it behind.  I have noticed more racism from those who did not serve only because they compete for jobs with the Vietnamese.  Reality.<br><br>
The future lies ahead and we must do our best with the past which we cannot change.
<p><code>--   (Silent Warrior) </code><p>


